reset

public void reset(boolean fireEvents)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeManager
Clear out the contents of this HyperEdgeManager. All HyperEdges, and Edges are removed.

Specified by:
reset in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
fireEvents - if true, HyperEdges will be removed in such a way that DeleteListener.objectDestroyed() events are fired at the expense of being slower to reset. If false, no objectDestroyed() events are fired, but resetting will be faster.

getHyperEdgesByNode

public java.util.Iterator<HyperEdge> getHyperEdgesByNode(giny.model.Node node,
                                                         giny.model.GraphPerspective gp)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeManager
Return an Iterator over all HyperEdges containing a given Node for a given GraphPerspective.

Specified by:
getHyperEdgesByNode in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
node - the Node contained within a HyperEdge. If null, node is not considered in the matching process and all HyperEdges satisfying gp are returned.
gp - the GraphPerspective within which the HyperEdge must belong. If null, all HyperEdges satisfying node are returned.
Returns:
a non-null, read-only Iterator (doesn't allow modification) over all matching HyperEdges. The iterator will contain all existing HyperEdges if both node and gp are null. The Iterator will be empty if no HyperEdge contains node, or if no HyperEdge within the given non-null gp contains the node.

Return an Iterator over all HyperEdges containing a collection of Nodes for a given GraphPerspective. These nodes do not include Connector Nodes.

Specified by:
getHyperEdgesByNodes in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
nodes - the Collection of Nodes that must all be contained within a HyperEdge. If null, nodes are not considered in the matching process and all HyperEdges satisfying gp are returned.
gp - the GraphPerspective within which the HyperEdge must belong. If null, all HyperEdges satisfying nodes are returned.
Returns:
a non-null, read-only Iterator (doesn't allow modification) over all matching HyperEdges. The iterator will contain all existing HyperEdges if both nodes and gp are null. The Iterator will be empty if nodes is empty, no HyperEdge contains the given set of nodes, or if no HyperEdge within the given non-null gp contains the set of nodes.

getHyperEdgesByEdgeTypes

public java.util.Iterator<HyperEdge> getHyperEdgesByEdgeTypes(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> edgeITypes,
                                                              giny.model.GraphPerspective gp)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeManager
Return an Iterator over all HyperEdges containing Nodes with Edges that match a given Collection of edge interaction types within a given GraphPerspective.

Specified by:
getHyperEdgesByEdgeTypes in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
edgeITypes - the Collection of String edge interaction types where each edge interaction type must match the interaction type attribute of a Edge contained within the HyperEdge. If null, edgeITypes are not considered in the matching process and all HyperEdges satisfying gp are returned.
gp - the GraphPerspective within which the HyperEdges must belong. If null, all HyperEdges satisfying edgeITypes are returned.
Returns:
a non-null, read-only Iterator (doesn't allow modification) over all matching HyperEdges. A HyperEdge matches iff for every edge interaction type in edgeITypes, there is a corresponding Edge whose interaction type attribute matches edge type. The iterator will contain all existing HyperEdges if both edgeITypes and gp are null. Iterator will be empty if no HyperEdge contains nodes that coorespond to the given edgeITypes, or if no HyperEdge within the given non-null gp contains nodes that coorespond to the given edgeITypes.

getNodesByEdgeTypes

public java.util.Iterator<giny.model.Node> getNodesByEdgeTypes(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> edgeITypes,
                                                               giny.model.GraphPerspective gp)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeManager
Return an Iterator over all distinct Nodes associated with Edges that match a given Collection of edge types within a given GraphPerspective. These nodes do not include Connector Nodes.

Specified by:
getNodesByEdgeTypes in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
edgeITypes - the Collection of String edge interaction types where each edge type must match the type of an Edge associated with a given Node. If null, edgeITypes are not considered in the matching process and all Nodes satisfying gp are returned.
gp - the GraphPerspective within which the Nodes must belong. If null, the GraphPerspective is not considered in the matching process and all Nodes satisfying edgeITypes are returned.
Returns:
a non-null, read-only Iterator (doesn't allow modification) over all distinct matching Nodes. A Node matches iff for every edge interaction type in edgeITypes, there is a corresponding Edge associated with this Node whose interaction type attribute matches edge type. The iterator will contain all Nodes found within any HyperEdge if both edgeITypes and gp are null. Iterator will be empty if edgeITypes is empty, no Node cooresponds to the given edgeITypes, or if no Node within the given non-null gp contains Nodes that coorespond to the given edgeITypes.
